Find Domain WHOIS is a free new tab extension which is integrated into Chrome and enables you to search for the domain records of websites, while you browse online. A search bar by Microsoft Bing enables you to surf the web at ease from the new tab.

How to get started
Once the new tab extension is downloaded and added to Chrome (browser), all you need to do is enter the website in the Enter Domain Name box and click search, following which you will be presented with the domain records including Registrant information, Administrative contact, Nameservers among others. The search engine on the new tab will change to Microsoft Bing once downloaded.

Features

Easy way to check domain information on your new tab
Reliable web search by Microsoft Bing
Completely free, with no additional permissions required
